cs.DS, cs.CG, cs.DM, cs.GT, cs.CC. 

The paper deals with graph theory and algorithms, which are typically categorized under cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) and cs.CG (Computational Geometry). The problem of finding efficient and perfect dominating sets also involves combinatorial optimization, which falls under cs.DM (Discrete Mathematics). The paper also discusses the complexity of the problem, which is related to computational complexity theory, and hence could be categorized under cs.CC (Computational Complexity).
